Atlus Pins Up SMTIV: Apocalypse Launch Edition
05.03.2016
ALEX FULLERNEWS DIRECTOR
Atlus recently announced the launch edition bonus for its upcoming release of Shin Megami Tensei IV: Apocalypse. In addition to the a copy of the game, those who pre-order or purchase a launch copy will receive set of three metallic pins. The pins are roughly 0.75" in diameter and feature Dagda's mark and the symbols for peace and anarachy, the two main routes of the game.
Released as Shin Megami Tensei IV: Final in Japan, Apocalypse is an entriely new game that takes place during the events of Shin Megami Tensei IV. Players are put into the role of a Hunter cadet that is killed by demons in post-apocalyptic Tokyo. The protagonist is brought back to life at the behest of the deity Dagda in return for his fealty. SMTIV: Apocalypse is set for release in North America this summer digitally and physically for Nintendo 3DS with a recommended retail price of $49.99/CDN$64.99.
